}'

Reports assignments to method receivers. When you assign a value to the method receiver, the value will not be reflected outside of the method itself. Values will be reflected in subsequent calls from the same method. Example: 'package main

import "fmt"

type demo struct {
 Val int
}

func (d *demo) change() {
 d = nil // Assignment to the method receiver propagates only to callees but not to callers
